<Author>ccwh
<Content>Would recommend it My boyfriend and I spend a long weekend in Barcelona, and were trying to find an affordable but comfortable hotel within reach of the main Las Ramblas area of Barcelona. We went on many review sites including Trip Advisor, and settled on the NH Sant Angelo based on the reviews given which said that it was a comfortable, and above average hotel. The hotel was easy to reach from the Arc De Triomph bus station (which connects to the Barcelona Girona airport) and it is less than a 10 minutes walk from the nearest Metro station. There are 3 Metro stations close by, along with Sant railway station. From the nearest Metro station, it is about 10 minutes to Las Ramblas (on the Metro) and about 20 minutes walk. The only drawback would be a slightly undersized room but this seems to be typical of most European hotels. The pics shown are accurately descriptive of the hotel, and the receptionist staff were all very friendly and instantly provided us with bus timetables when requested.The best thing about the hotel was the breakfast which came included within the price. It was a buffet breakfast, and consisted of pastries, croissants, cereals, yoghurts and drinks, juices, fruits, cold meats, scrambled eggs and chorizos. This was one of the widest array of choices in a buffet breakfast that we've had so far for the level of hotel.We would recommend this hotel if you are searching for an affordable and comfortable hotel with a good level of service. 
